Mexico Stocks: Elektra, Liverpool, Penoles Decline; Modelo Gains

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-09-12T16:16:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/mexico-stocks-elektra-liverpool-penoles-decline-modelo-gains.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:48 a.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index fell 0.9 percent to 33,523.24.  Mexican stocks fell as speculation  Germany  is preparing for
a Greek debt default curbed demand for higher-yielding,
emerging-market assets.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM), the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , plunged 6.7
percent to 1,029.05 pesos. El Puerto de Liverpool SAB (LIVEPOLC
MM), a luxury-goods retailer, fell 2.8 percent to 87.2 pesos.  Consumer staples stocks gained as demand increased for
equities that are less vulnerable to global economic risks.  Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC MM), Mexico’s largest beer maker,
rose 0.8 percent to 70.75 pesos. Fomento Economico Mexicano SAB
(FEMSAUBD MM),  Latin America ’s largest Coca-Cola bottler,
advanced 0.8 percent to 82.05 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, fell 3 percent to 573.40 pesos. Silver for
December delivery in New York slipped as much as 2.6 percent to
$40.55 an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
